                <h1>Will an Arrest Show on a Background Check if Not Convicted?</h1>
                <p>If you were arrested but not convicted, the arrest may still appear on a background check, depending on the type of check conducted. Some checks, like those for employment, may reveal arrest records even if charges were dropped. It's essential to be aware of local laws as they can vary regarding how long arrest records are retained.</p>
